Dear Dr. Goodwin:

Thank you for your answer. Please let me ask you a couple of more
questions.

1. The code now compiles well. But two functions return weird values.
One is speciesIndex() which returns -2147483648 for every spcies when
it should return an integer between 1 and 109. The other one is
meanMolecularWeight() which returns something like 137887672. when it
should return about 25. Do you have any idea about these things?

2. I&#39;m going to model soot formation in a premixed flame. I&#39;m
wondering if &quot;Burner stabilized and axisymmetric stagnation
point-flame&quot; is the same as &quot;1-dimensional premixed flame&quot; which is
frequently studied in the literature. Do you have any manual for this
flame? The URL for &quot;Documented Python Code&quot; in
http://rayleigh.cds.caltech.edu/~goodwin/cantera/documentation.html
does not work. In addition, do you have any plan to make a Fortran
version of that code?

Thanks in advance.


